Minister of Youths and Sports Development, Sunday Dare, who hit the ground running with  series of activities upon his appointment, is leaving no stone unturned as he embarked on a tour of stadia in Nigeria, with  a promise of complete transformation of the Sports sector.
Some  of the Stadia he visited include  the Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja, the Ahmadu Bello Stadium in Kaduna and the Telslim Balogun Stadium Lagos, where he watched the Falcons triumph over their opponents. The Minister also held series of meetings with stakeholders in order to move Sports forward the country.
Stakeholders agree that the astute administrator’s greatest strength remains his unwavering passion to see to the transformation of the Sports sector before the expiration of the administration’s tenure.






			
